*Determination of the number of moles:*
  The molar mass of atomic nitrogen is $14 " g/mol"$, which means the molar mass of $N_2$ is $28 " g/mol"$.
  $ n = m / M = (1.60 " g") / (28 " g/mol") = 0.057 " mol" $

  *Initial state (state 1):*
  $ P_1 = 1.01 times 10^5 " Pa", quad T_1 = 0^degree C = 273.15 " K" $
  Using the ideal gas law ($P V = n R T$) gives:
  $ V_1 = (n dot R dot T_1) / P_1 = (0.057 " mol" times 8.314 " J mol"^(-1) "K"^(-1) times 273.15 " K") / (1.01 times 10^5 " Pa") = 0.0013 " m"^3 $

  *Final state (state 2):*
  The piston is moved so that the pressure becomes $120 " kPa"$. Since the process occurs slowly and in equilibrium with the surroundings, the temperature does not change (isothermal process):
  $ P_2 = 120 " kPa", quad T_2 = T_1 \
  n dot R dot T = "constant" => P_1 V_1 = P_2 V_2 $
  This yields the new volume:
  $ V_2 = P_1 / P_2 times V_1 = 101 / 120 times 0.0013 " m"^3 = 0.0011 " m"^3 $